You can use the Node.js driver to build an aggregation pipeline by creating a
pipeline variable or passing aggregation stages directly into the aggregation
method. See the following examples to learn more about each of these approaches.**Pipeline-definition:**Create a Pipeline```javascript
// Defines the aggregation pipeline
const pipeline = [
  { $match: { ... } },
  { $group: { ... } }
];

// Executes the aggregation pipeline
const results = await collection.aggregate(pipeline);
```**Pipeline-direct:**Direct Aggregation```javascript
// Defines and executes the aggregation pipeline
const results = await collection.aggregate([
  { $match: { ... } },
  { $group: { ... } }
]);
```

